parseAlias

private java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> parseAlias(java.lang.String aliasMapString)
Parses the received value of Alias source pattern and values in a string and updates the map.

Parameters:
aliasMapString - The comples string containg all the entries made on the configuration form. Entries of two consecutive rows are separated by /$$CRLF$$/ A Source pattern is separated by its corresponding Alias pattern by /$$EQUAL$$/
Returns:
A Map depicting the actual mapping specified by the user on the configuration page

isIncludeMetadata

public boolean isIncludeMetadata(java.lang.String metadata)
Check if the Metadata can be included or not. Applies two level filter: Level1: Only those metadata which are specified under included_metadata should be included. If included_metadata is empty, include all. Level2: exclude all metadata which are spcified under excluded_metadata.

Parameters:
metadata - Metadata to be checked
